1
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:11,130
Wangshu,

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,000
look.

3
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,520
Just as you taught me,

4
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:14,920
I have sorted everything out.

5
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:16,320
Not bad, sister-in-law.

6
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,120
You are the smartest

7
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,650
letter office apprentice I have ever taught.

8
00:01:26,039 --> 00:01:26,800
Excuse me,

9
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,860
is the letter office open?

10
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:30,640
Yes.

11
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,560
This is Lin family's Wansheng Letter Office,

12
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,520
Quanzhou branch.

13
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,780
We will open tomorrow.

14
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:37,880
That's great.

15
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,680
Hurry up and help me check

16
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:42,080
if there's a letter from Malaya.

17
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:45,560
My son's name is Pan Jiu.

18
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:48,160
I'm from Qianxi Village, Quanzhou.

19
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:49,680
Okay.

20
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:50,400
Ma'am,

21
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:51,240
don't worry.

22
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:52,160
Please sit down first.

23
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,490
I'll look for it for you.

24
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:56,320
When did your son

25
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,360
go to Nanyang?

26
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,120
Look.

27
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,080
This is my son.

28
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:06,370
He went to Nanyang seven years ago.

29
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:10,080
There has been no news from him since.

30
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,560
I've been waiting

31
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,000
and waiting.

32
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,360
But no letters came.

33
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,740
I don't know if he's dead or alive.

34
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:20,560
I...

35
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,240
I just can't accept it.

36
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:31,810
Grandma.

37
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,680
The letters in the agency

38
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,120
were messed up when the Japanese

39
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,450
bombed us a few days ago.

40
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,820
We are still sorting them out.

41
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:39,820
How about this?

42
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,520
You go home and rest first.

43
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:42,640
If we find his letters,

44
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,120
we will deliver them to you immediately.

45
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:44,600
Okay?

46
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,079
Okay.

47
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,440
Tell me,

48
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,440
is my son still alive?

49
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,560
Alive. He must be alive.

50
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,810
Don't worry.

51
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,420
It's good that he's alive.

52
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,040
As long as he's alive.

53
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,400
This child,

54
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,160
why hasn't he sent a letter?

55
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:15,760
Eat.

56
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,320
Let's talk after you're full.

57
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:17,650
Okay.

58
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,079
Slow down.

59
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,260
If you choke to death, who do I ask?

60
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:34,329
Brother Jiu,

61
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:37,880
judging from your accent, you're also from Quanzhou.

62
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,250
Qianxi Village, Quanzhou.

63
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,650
Qianxi Village.

64
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,400
I know it.

65
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:46,000
There is a Confucian temple at the east end of the village.

66
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,860
How do you know?

67
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,280
I've delivered remittances there.

68
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,000
There are many

69
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,280
overseas Chinese from Malaya.

70
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,940
Many of them are surnamed Pan.

71
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,360
You really are a remittance courier.

72
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:55,960
Yes.

73
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:57,140
I didn't lie to you.

74
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,240
I work at the

75
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:01,120
Lin family's Wansheng Remittance Agency in Malaya.

76
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,440
I frequently travel back and forth to Quanzhou.

77
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,040
Quanzhou also has

78
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,680
a branch of Wansheng Remittance Agency.

79
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,120
The Lin family in Malaya.

80
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:07,580
I know them.

81
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,560
There is such a business.

82
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:11,810
Brother Jiu,

83
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,490
have you been to Malaya?

84
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,160
I went overseas seven years ago.

85
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:22,840
Then why are you now...

86
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,050
Seven years ago,

87
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,080
I was 28

88
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,080
and had just gotten married.

89
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:27,840
The owner of the wet market

90
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,040
where I worked,

91
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,930
that lecherous bald Huang,

92
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,520
ruined my wife,

93
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:37,050
forcing her to drown herself in the river.

94
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:38,800
In a fit of rage,

95
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,330
I chopped him to pieces.

96
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,700
The government came to arrest me.

97
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:48,960
I snuck onto a boat overnight

98
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,020
and fled to Malaya.

99
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,920
Then why are you now back...

100
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,480
Who knew bald Huang's family

101
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,280
was rich?

102
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,680
They sent people all the way to Malaya,

103
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,960
bribed the local police,

104
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,160
and wanted to kill me.

105
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,690
Having no other choice,

106
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,840
I took a few poor brothers

107
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,320
and fled to an island.

108
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:10,680
We specialized in robbing

109
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:13,560
the cargo ships of black-hearted merchants passing by.

110
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:15,360
I didn't expect that a while ago,

111
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,960
the island would be bombed by the Japanese.

112
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:20,040
Many brothers were killed by the bombing.

113
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:20,760
Only

114
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,730
Ah San, Ah Si, and I are left.

115
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:26,210
We had nowhere to go.

116
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,650
So we fled back here.

117
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,400
I just arrived,

118
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,650
and you delivered yourself to my door.

119
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:39,440
It seems

120
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,890
we are destined to meet.

121
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,090
It seems you are also

122
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:45,380
a miserable person, Brother Jiu.

123
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:51,920
What is this?

124
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,650
Sister-in-law,

125
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:55,690
Grandma Pan has had a hard life.

126
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,040
Nine times out of ten,

127
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,500
her son is no longer alive.

128
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,000
I can't bear to see her sad.

129
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,480
If she comes to the remittance agency again,

130
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,010
give her these few dollars.

131
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,240
Tell her it was sent

132
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:05,920
by her son.

133
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:06,560
Okay?

134
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:09,640
Okay.

135
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:17,200
Drink.

136
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:24,450
Brother Jiu.

137
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,320
The soldiers fighting against the Japanese at the front

138
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,280
are just like us,

139
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,720
poor people.

140
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:30,960
But they are risking their lives

141
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,000
at the front

142
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,740
to defend our country.

143
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,920
The medicine and money I brought

144
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,360
were collected for them.

145
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,980
I beg you, Brother Jiu,

146
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,280
please return them to me

147
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:42,240
so I can send them to the soldiers as soon as possible.

148
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,080
Don't think I'll believe you

149
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,200
just because

150
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,450
you told me this.

151
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,400
Then

152
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,200
how can I make you believe me?

153
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,880
You have to make me trust you.

154
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:52,170
Brother Jiu,

155
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,120
do you have any family

156
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,760
at home in Qianxi Village?

157
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:56,840
Only my mother.

158
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:00,520
Have you ever seen her?

159
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,200
I've been on the wanted list.

160
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,660
How could I dare to go back?

161
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,760
That is to say,

162
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,210
since you escaped here,

163
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,640
you haven't seen her

164
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,050
or sent her any letters.

165
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,360
I don't know if she

166
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,400
is still alive.

167
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,640
As a son,

168
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,330
I'm so unfilial.

169
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:25,650
Brother Jiu,

170
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:26,480
I have a way

171
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,380
to fulfill your filial piety.

172
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:30,970
What do you mean?

173
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,280
I can write a letter for you

174
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,060
and send it to Grandma Pan.

175
00:07:36,159 --> 00:07:36,960
I'll deliver it in person

176
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,280
to your home in Qianxi Village

177
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,440
and tell her

178
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,440
that you are working in Nanyang

179
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:42,560
and everything is fine.

180
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,840
When she receives this letter,

181
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:44,640
she'll believe

182
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,920
you are really working in Nanyang

183
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,680
as an honest man earning your own living.

184
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,600
Then she will have hope

185
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,260
to live well

186
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:50,760
and wait for you to return safely.

187
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:51,240
Okay.

188
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,370
If you can do this

189
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,040
for me,

190
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:56,560
I will return all your things

191
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,320
without keeping a single one.

192
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:58,980
It's a deal.

193
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,170
Never go back on my word.

194
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,880
I'm off to deliver the letters.

195
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,040
Dad, you're getting old.

196
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,680
You must be careful on the mountain roads.

197
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,040
I'm an experienced courier.

198
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,770
Don't worry.

199
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,680
Take care, Uncle Lin.

200
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,159
The fourth house ahead.

201
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,559
One, two, three.

202
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,080
Granny,

203
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,640
is this Pan Jiu's house?

204
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:53,640
Who are you?

205
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:54,610
I'm a courier

206
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,120
from Wansheng Courier Station in Quanzhou.

207
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,720
I'm here to deliver letters.

208
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,920
Is it a letter from Pan Jiu's family?

209
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:00,960
Yes, it is.

210
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,360
Please come in.

211
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,560
Come in.

212
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:12,880
Have a seat.

213
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:14,650
Thank you, Grandma.

214
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,260
Have some water first.

215
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:21,200
Okay.

216
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,040
Young man,

217
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,520
say it again,

218
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,980
who is the letter from?

219
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:32,240
It's a letter from your son, Pan Jiu,

220
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,680
sent from Malaya.

221
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,480
The Bodhisattva has answered my prayers.

222
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,000
Grandma.

223
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,560
Please don't.

224
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,400
The Bodhisattva has come to my door.

225
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,200
Please don't.

226
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,160
Please don't.

227
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:40,880
Sit down.

228
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:42,680
Sit down.

229
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,680
I...

230
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:47,720
This

231
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:48,680
is the letter your son

232
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:49,720
sent to you.

233
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,420
I'll read it to you.

234
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:02,400
To my dearest mother,

235
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,400
I have been away from home for nearly eight years

236
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,000
and think of you constantly.

237
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,520
I deeply regret that I cannot serve you day and night

238
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:10,560
while I am away.

239
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:13,320
My parents gave birth to me and raised me.

240
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,120
Now we are far apart.

241
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,240
I cannot serve you by your side.

242
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,280
I am ashamed

243
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:19,980
and deeply guilty.

244
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,960
I am sending 10 silver dollars with this letter.

245
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,400
Please accept and use them.

246
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:25,920
I am doing well in Nanyang.

247
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,490
Please do not worry.

248
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,200
Look.

249
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,000
This is from your son,

250
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,720
the 10 silver dollars for you.

251
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,640
Take a look.

252
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,720
My great benefactor!

253
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,290
How can I ever thank you?

254
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:46,080
Grandma.

255
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,800
I am the courier delivering the remittances.

256
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,440
You're welcome.

257
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,840
It's the least I could do.

258
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:51,600
Young man,

259
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,960
what is your name?

260
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,610
My name is Chen Jiadong.

261
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,880
Chen Jiadong.

262
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,000
Chen as in the surname,

263
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,930
Jia as in nation,

264
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,280
and Dong as in pillar.

265
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,520
Young man,

266
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,130
could you please

267
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,480
send this photo

268
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,160
to my son?

269
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:09,360
Tell him

270
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,730
that Mom is still alive.

271
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:13,480
I will wait for the day he returns.

272
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,650
Rest assured, Grandma.

273
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:17,560
I will definitely deliver it.
